answers.answer: I am 34 weeks today and just last week i went to the dr for swelling of my ankles and calves. I had protein in my urine as well and my dr told me could be possible dehydration and the heat. My bp is always good as well.My dr isnt worried about pre eclampsia she said if the bp is anything higher than 140/90 it would be a concern

question: I just got back from my 34w appointment and my dr said there was quite a bit of protein in my urine this time.  Up until this point, the tests have always come back negative.  My blood pressure was 118/72, and has always been excellent and I have only gained 20lbs during pregnancy.  Before becoming pregnant, I was probably 10-15lbs over weight already.Are there any other reasons for increased protein in the urine other than preeclampsia?
title: Preeclampsia?
